
[1]soda

   SO'DA, n. Mineral fixed alkali; natron; so called because it forms the
   basis of marine salt. It is found native in Egypt; but it is generally
   obtained form the salsola kali. Soda is an oxyd, or the protoxyd of
   sodiem, a metal.
